<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-05-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-05-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="1287" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1287">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.63/96.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Special Agent <persName type="from">Carothers</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Gomez Palacio</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-05-19">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 19, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Referring Department’s May 17, I have no fear of enforcement of decrees.
                            I will be in Chihuahua in two days and will take matter up final
                            adjustment but have assurance that there will be no enforcement
                            especially against foreigners.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Carothers.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>